    "text": {
      "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b><a href=\"/Main_Page\" title=\"Main Page\">Home</a> * <a href=\"/People\" title=\"People\">People</a> * Tom Kerrigan</b>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"http://www.bizjournals.com/seattle/stories/2009/01/12/story13.html\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/f/fd/TomKerrigan.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"157\" class=\"thumbimage\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/File:TomKerrigan.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Tom Kerrigan, creator of <a href=\"/index.php?title=TChess&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"TChess (page does not exist)\">tChess</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></div></div></div> \n<p><b>Thomas C. (Tom) Kerrigan</b>,<br />\nan American software developer and computer chess programmer, who already got hooked on computer chess as a 13-year-old growing up in <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fort_Collins,_Colorado\">Fort Collins, Colorado</a>, playing the <a href=\"/Chessmaster\" title=\"Chessmaster\">Chessmaster</a> on a friend's <a href=\"/IBM_PC\" title=\"IBM PC\">PC</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>. Inspired by the 1978 articles by <a href=\"/Peter_W._Frey\" title=\"Peter W. Frey\">Peter W. Frey</a> and <a href=\"/Larry_Atkin\" title=\"Larry Atkin\">Larry Atkin</a> on <a href=\"/Chess_0.5\" title=\"Chess 0.5\">Chess 0.5</a> in <a href=\"/Byte_Magazine#BYTE310\" title=\"Byte Magazine\">BYTE magazine</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>, he started the development his chess program <a href=\"/Stobor\" title=\"Stobor\">Stobor</a> in 1993, and further wrote the didactic open source chess program <a href=\"/TSCP\" title=\"TSCP\">TSCP</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>. While still focusing on Stobor and its <a href=\"/Parallel_Search\" title=\"Parallel Search\">parallel search</a>, Tom Kerrigan's recent project is <a href=\"/index.php?title=TChess&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"TChess (page does not exist)\">tChess</a>,  a chess program for the <a href=\"/index.php?title=IPhone&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"IPhone (page does not exist)\">iPhone</a> and <a href=\"/index.php?title=IPod_touch&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"IPod touch (page does not exist)\">iPod touch</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Forum_Posts\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Forum Posts</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#1997_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">1997 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#2000_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2000 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#2015_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2015 ...</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#External_Links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External Links</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Forum_Posts\">Forum Posts</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Tom_Kerrigan&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Forum Posts\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"1997_...\">1997 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Tom_Kerrigan&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: 1997 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://groups.google.com/group/rec.games.chess.computer/browse_frm/thread/bbeb808d4bac07e5\">Going commercial, maybe</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Tom C. Kerrigan</a>, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">rgcc</a>, March 04, 1997</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=21856\">piece list possibilities</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Tom Kerrigan</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, July 07, 1998&#160;» <a href=\"/Piece-Lists\" title=\"Piece-Lists\">Piece-Lists</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=22472\">is the \"dead bit\" a good idea?</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Tom Kerrigan</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, July 20, 1998&#160;» <a href=\"/Piece-Lists\" title=\"Piece-Lists\">Piece-Lists</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=23632\">New version of TSCP!</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Tom Kerrigan</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, August 02, 1998</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=24043\">TSCP derivatives?</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Tom Kerrigan</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, August 06, 1998</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2000_...\">2000 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Tom_Kerrigan&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: 2000 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=92614\">Chip design project &amp; another request for Belle/DT/DB info</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Tom Kerrigan</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, January 27, 2000&#160;» <a href=\"/FPGA\" title=\"FPGA\">FPGA</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=112849\">tip for \"simulating\" an MP computer &amp; performance of ABDADA</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Tom Kerrigan</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, May 28, 2000&#160;»  <a href=\"/ABDADA\" title=\"ABDADA\">ABDADA</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=280383\">New version of TSCP (1.8)--opening book and hash keys</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Tom Kerrigan</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, January 30, 2003</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=283740\">IA-64 vs OOOE (attn Taylor, Hyatt)</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Tom Kerrigan</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, February 11, 2003 &#160;» <a href=\"/Itanium\" title=\"Itanium\">Itanium</a>, <a href=\"/X86-64\" title=\"X86-64\">x86-64</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2015_...\">2015 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Tom_Kerrigan&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: 2015 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=56936\">Possible improvement to ABDADA -- checking for cutoffs</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Tom Kerrigan</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, July 10, 2015&#160;» <a href=\"/ABDADA\" title=\"ABDADA\">ABDADA</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=56937\">Actual speedups from YBWC and ABDADA on 8+ core machines?</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Tom Kerrigan</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, July 10, 2015&#160;» <a href=\"/ABDADA\" title=\"ABDADA\">ABDADA</a>, <a href=\"/Young_Brothers_Wait_Concept\" title=\"Young Brothers Wait Concept\">Young Brothers Wait Concept</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=63023\">Good parallel speedup with ABDADA and cutoff checks</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Tom Kerrigan</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, February 03, 2017</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=65011\">\"How To\" guide to parallel-izing an engine</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Tom Kerrigan</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, August 27, 2017</li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_Links\">External Links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Tom_Kerrigan&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: External Links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.tckerrigan.com/\">Tom Kerrigan's Home Page</a></li></ul>\n<dl><dd> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.tckerrigan.com/Misc/Multiplayer_Elo/\">Multiplayer Elo</a></dd></dl>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.game-ai-forum.org/icga-tournaments/person.php?id=76\">Tom Kerrigan's ICGA Tournaments</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Tom_Kerrigan&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.bizjournals.com/seattle/stories/2009/01/12/story13.html\">iPhone apps ring income for former Microsoftie Kerrigan</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://seattle.bizjournals.com/seattle/\">Puget Sound Business Journal (Seattle)</a>, January 9, 2009</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.bizjournals.com/seattle/stories/2009/01/12/story13.html\">iPhone apps ring income for former Microsoftie Kerrigan</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://seattle.bizjournals.com/seattle/\">Puget Sound Business Journal (Seattle)</a>, January 9, 2009</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"/Peter_W._Frey\" title=\"Peter W. Frey\">Peter W. Frey</a>, <a href=\"/Larry_Atkin\" title=\"Larry Atkin\">Larry Atkin</a> (<b>1978</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.computerhistory.org/chess/full_record.php?iid=doc-431614f6d5ba2\">Creating a Chess Player</a>.</i> An Essay on Human and Computer Chess Skill, <a href=\"/Byte_Magazine#BYTE310\" title=\"Byte Magazine\">BYTE, Vol. 3, No. 10</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.tckerrigan.com/Chess/TSCP\">TSCP - Tom Kerrigan's Home Page</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.tchessgame.com/\">tChess, Chess for the iPhone and iPod touch!</a></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n<p><b><a href=\"/People\" title=\"People\">Up one level</a></b>\n</p>\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260228171047\nCache expiry: 86400\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.017 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.019 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 97/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 206/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 0/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 0/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 2/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%    0.000      1 -total\n-->\n</div>\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key oscar70_mw1-mw_:pcache:idhash:3221-0!canonical and timestamp 20260228171047 and revision id 8851\n -->\n"
